-- Agricultural Bank Is a Proxy for Economic Growth in Rural China, Liu Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-07T04:15:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/agricultural-bank-is-a-proxy-for-economic-growth-in-rural-china-liu-says.html

          
          
             Agricultural Bank of China Ltd. is a
“must buy” for investors as it is a proxy for the development
of the nation’s rural areas, Atlantis Investment Management
Ltd.’s Liu Yang said in a Bloomberg Television interview.  
 Agricultural Bank of China is raising at least $19.2
billion in what may become the world’s biggest initial public
offering, according to people with knowledge of the pricing for
Hong Kong and Shanghai.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
